# Backend env layout (copy snippets into `.env.local` for overrides — gitignored)

## Files
- `.env.development` — committed defaults for **local** Postgres/API (`npm run dev`).
- `.env.production.example` — placeholders only; copy to `.env.production` locally if needed for prod-mode smoke tests.
- `.env.local` — optional overrides (secrets); gitignored.

`NODE_ENV=production` + `npm run start` loads `.env.production`.

See `docs/ENVIRONMENT.md` at repo root for commands.

## Keys

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/cbp_db"
JWT_SECRET=""
JWT_EXPIRES_IN="7d"

# Matches cbp-frontend INTERNAL_FRONTEND_AUTH_SECRET (Next `/api/auth/sync-backend-session` → POST /auth/internal/trusted-session)
INTERNAL_FRONTEND_AUTH_SECRET=""
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
OTP_SKIP_CODE_VALIDATION=
ADMIN_API_KEY=

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=
AWS_S3_BUCKET=

# Optional: SES defaults to AWS_* credentials. Use separate keys when the S3 IAM user lacks ses:SendEmail.
# AWS_SES_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SES_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_SES_REGION=
# Optional production: set to true only when SES is configured (otherwise production skips SES).
# EMAIL_SENDING_ENABLED=

FLEX_BASE_URL=
FLEX_CLIENT_ID=
FLEX_CLIENT_SECRET=
FLEX_USER_CODE=
FLEX_RAW_PASSWORD=
